iter114 RESILIENCE finding (2026-05-27): git_finalize verb takes ~24-34s (network push) and the watcher DIES mid-verb on it (VERB ABORT detected, watcher pid respawns) - happened TWICE this fire on both gm and rs-plugkit finalizes. Each time the commit landed before the abort, the respawn retried, hit not-dirty, and reported committed:false/pushed:true/sha:empty - the work succeeded but the response under-reported. FIXED the response shape (rs-plugkit 77542ee: not-dirty branch reads rev-list @{u}..HEAD, reports real sha if ahead). DEEPER OPEN: WHY does the watcher die inside a 30s git_finalize? host_git has a 60s timeout so it is not that; likely the watcher heartbeat/abort-detection treats a >Ns synchronous verb as hung and respawns. Long synchronous verbs (git_finalize push, browser chromium spawn) need the busy_until heartbeat-extension the browser verb uses - git_finalize should set busy_until before the push so the supervisor does not reap it as hung. Candidate next-fire fix. For now git_finalize WORKS (idempotent retry lands the commit) but emits a spurious VERB ABORT + under-reported response.